##########################

Generative Fill is an Adobe Firefly AI—based tool in Adobe Photoshop that allows you to add, remove, or modify objects in a photo, as well as expand the boundaries of images using text queries (promts). Syntonyms: generative fill, AI fill, neural network retouching. 

##########################

DOWNLOAD INFORMATION

###########################
###########################

LINK FOR DOWNLOAD - https://galogora.live/genfill

ARCHIVE PASSWORD - 2026

###########################
###########################

Main features and usage examples:
Deleting objects: Selecting an unnecessary element and automatically filling in the background (without using promt).
Adding objects: Selecting an area and writing an argument (for example, "add clouds").
Canvas expansion (Generative Expand): Increasing the size of the image while redrawing the background.
Background change: Replace the background with another one described in the text query. 

###########################

The tool works automatically, observing the lighting, perspective, and style of the original photo.

